annotationA: DnaJ homolog shv; Maintains stem cell niche architecture in the testes. Activates an extracellular integrin beta-PS pathway which regulates DE-cadherin (shg) levels in somatic hub cells, and is essential for maintaining the number of germline stem cells and the structure and localization of hub cells
annotationB: Protein disulfide-isomerase A6 homolog; Calcium-binding protein 1 (CaBP1) resides in the lumen of the endoplasmic reticulum. CaBP1 seems to be relocated outside cells during apoptosis and involved in the phagocytosis of apoptotic cells
